 1142","1222":"1222","1145":"1145","1207":"1207","Acre, Northern, Îsraîl":"Acre, Northern, Israël","Verdun-sur-Meuse, Meuse, Lorraine, Frankrijk":"Verdun, Meuse, Lorraine, Frankrijk"},"en":{"um 1142–26 November 1190":"about 1142–26 November 1190","1140–Female":"1140–Deceased","1142–1190":"1142–1190","1145–1207":"1145–1207","1142–1206":"1142–1206","1162–1222":"1162–1222","1115–1163":"1115–1163","1120–1163":"1120–1163","1190":"1190","1120":"1120","1142":"1142","1163":"1163","26 November 1190":"26 November 1190","1162":"1162","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1206":"1206","Abt 1163":"about 1163","1115":"1115","um 1142":"about 1142","1222":"1222","1145":"1145","1207":"1207","Acre, Northern, Îsraîl":"Acre, Northern, Israel","Verdun-sur-Meuse, Meuse, Lorraine, Frankrijk":"Verdun, Meuse, Lorraine, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Gobert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gobert V d'Aspremont Baron by Saint Louis was born about 1142, in Verdun, Meuse, Lorraine, France, his father, Gobert d'Aspremont IV, was 29 and his mother, Adélaïde de Dun, was 24. He married Ida de Chiny in 1160. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 26 November 1190, in Acre, Northern, Israel, at the age of 49."},"et":{"um 1142–26 November 1190":"umbes 1142–26. november 1190","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1142–1190":"1142–1190","1145–1207":"1145–1207","1142–1206":"1142–1206","1162–1222":"1162–1222","1115–1163":"1115–1163","1120–1163":"1120–1163","1190":"1190","1120":"1120","1142":"1142","1163":"1163","26 November 1190":"26. november 1190","1162":"1162","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1206":"1206","Abt 1163":"umbes 1163","1115":"1115","um 1142":"umbes 1142","1222":"1222","1145":"1145","1207":"1207","Acre, Northern, Îsraîl":"Acre, Northern, Iisrael","Verdun-sur-Meuse, Meuse, Lorraine, Frankrijk":"Verdun, Meuse, Lorraine, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"um 1142–26 November 1190":"noin 1142–26. marraskuuta 1190","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1142–1190":"1142–1190","1145–1207":"1145–1207","1142–1206":"1142–1206","1162–1222":"1162–1222","1115–1163":"1115–1163","1120–1163":"1120–1163","1190":"1190","1120":"1120","1142":"1142","1163":"1163","26 November 1190":"26. marraskuuta 1190","1162":"1162","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1206":"1206","Abt 1163":"noin 1163","1115":"1115","um 1142":"noin 1142","1222":"1222","1145":"1145","1207":"1207","Acre, Northern, Îsraîl":"Acre, Northern, Israel","Verdun-sur-Meuse, Meuse, Lorraine, Frankrijk":"Verdun, Meuse, Lorraine, Ranska"},"fr":{"um 1142–26 November 1190":"environ 1142–26 novembre 1190","1140–Female":"1140–Décédée","1142–1190":"1142–1190","1145–1207":"1145–1207","1142–1206":"1142–1206","1162–1222":"1162–1222","1115–1163":"1115–1163","1120–1163":"1120–1163","1190":"1190","1120":"1120","1142":"1142","1163":"1163","26 November 1190":"26 novembre 1190","1162":"1162","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1206":"1206","Abt 1163":"environ 1163","1115":"1115","um 1142":"environ 1142","1222":"1222","1145":"1145","1207":"1207","Acre, Northern, Îsraîl":"Acre, Northern, Israël","Verdun-sur-Meuse, Meuse